Package jetbrains.mps.core.aspects.constraints.rules

Class LegacyAndRulesConstraintsDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.core.aspects.constraints.rules.LegacyAndRulesConstraintsDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RulesConstraintsDescriptor
    public final class LegacyAndRulesConstraintsDescriptor
extends Object
implements RulesConstraintsDescriptor
    Temporal adapter, it is supposed to be used until the new functionality completely replaces the older one Here we combine legacy canBe* and new (rules) canBe* constraints Basic idea is for the legacy functions to dominate the rules. So we have the old inheritance logic for the legacy canBe* functions + check all the rules for the hierarchy which are not being dominated by any canBe* function. We say that the rule is dominated by canBe* function if there is a canBe* function defined at the concept of rule or any its subconcept.
